In the following list, titles cited with quotation marks refer to captions that Ruskin wrote directly on the tour sketch, and titles cited with quotation marks inside square brackets 
                    refer to captions devised by W. G. Collingwood. Titles that are not Ruskinʼs, 
                    or that cannot be definitely traced to him, are cited without quotation marks. Citation here of Ruskin, Works, volume 38, 
                    refers to the “Catalogue of Ruskinʼs Drawings” compiled for the Library Edition (38:215–306); 
                    Collingwood, Life and Work of John Ruskin refers to the 
                    “Catalogue of Drawings by Mr. Ruskin (1829–1859)” (1:238–43); 
                    Collingwood, Ruskin Exhibition, 
                    refers to the catalogue of the Ruskin Memorial Exhibition, Mechanicsʼ Institute, Coniston (1900); 
                    Manchester City Art Gallery, Catalogue of the Ruskin Exhibition refers to the 
                    Ruskin Exhibition, Manchester (1904).
